01:04:50.330 --> 01:04:53.160
<font color="#ffff00">♪</font>

01:04:57.300 --> 01:05:00.300
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHISPERS)</font>:{\c} Clarence Wendell Crumb.

01:05:00.300 --> 01:05:02.610
<font color="#ff00ff">(MOUTHING)</font>

01:05:14.690 --> 01:05:18.720
<font color="#ff00ff">(CHUCKLING SOFTLY)</font>

01:05:20.860 --> 01:05:22.430
Take a little bit
of grape seed extract,

01:05:22.430 --> 01:05:23.860
and it'll keep it all in there.

01:05:23.860 --> 01:05:25.730
You'll absorb it
into your body faster.

01:05:25.730 --> 01:05:27.430
Let me ask you,
how much water you drinking?

01:05:27.430 --> 01:05:30.730
- Not enough.
- Yeah. I know.

01:05:30.730 --> 01:05:32.870
<font color="#ff00ff">(COMPUTERS WHIRRING QUIETLY)</font>

01:05:35.240 --> 01:05:37.170
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHEELS SQUEAKING SOFTLY)</font>

01:05:47.450 --> 01:05:48.980
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCANNER BEEPS, ALARM BUZZES)</font>

01:05:48.990 --> 01:05:50.920
<font color="#ff00ff">(DOOR OPENS)</font>

01:05:51.920 --> 01:05:54.090
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHEELS SQUEAKING SOFTLY)</font>

01:05:54.090 --> 01:05:56.690
<font color="#ff00ff">(SIGHS)</font>

01:05:56.690 --> 01:05:58.160
<font color="#138ce9">PATRICIA:</font> How?

01:05:58.160 --> 01:06:02.870
How did you get here
without anyone seeing?

01:06:02.870 --> 01:06:05.030
<font color="#138ce9">ELIJAH:</font> The sound of
a car backfiring occurs

01:06:05.040 --> 01:06:08.300
when unburned fuel vapor is
ignited by a very hot muffler

01:06:08.310 --> 01:06:10.240
upon the car being turned off.

01:06:10.240 --> 01:06:12.240
Daryl, who takes over
at 11:{\c}00 p.m.,

01:06:12.240 --> 01:06:14.780
suffers from this particular
vehicular malady.

01:06:14.780 --> 01:06:17.710
It happened seven minutes ago.

01:06:17.720 --> 01:06:19.880
Couple that with the fact
that I've overheard complaints

01:06:19.880 --> 01:06:22.050
about how long it takes him
to get to his desk...

01:06:22.050 --> 01:06:24.090
he's a bit of a talker,
you see...

01:06:24.090 --> 01:06:26.990
I estimate I have
two to three minutes left.

01:06:26.990 --> 01:06:30.460
Someone has been pretending.

01:06:30.460 --> 01:06:31.930
Pilfered the aspirin bottle.

01:06:31.930 --> 01:06:34.760
Replaced the original dose
of medicine

01:06:34.770 --> 01:06:36.470
with the same amount
of aspirin.

01:06:36.470 --> 01:06:37.930
Did sleight of hand
with the pills

01:06:37.940 --> 01:06:40.400
given to me to take daily.

01:06:40.400 --> 01:06:42.740
<font color="#138ce9">PATRICIA:</font> What do you want?

01:06:42.740 --> 01:06:44.810
<font color="#138ce9">ELIJAH:</font> Ma'am.

01:06:44.810 --> 01:06:47.110
I'm here to see

01:06:47.110 --> 01:06:49.950
if the tales of the
extraordinary being are real,

01:06:49.950 --> 01:06:52.950
- the half-man, half-creature.
- Patricia.

01:06:52.950 --> 01:06:55.690
But I appreciate your manners.

01:06:58.920 --> 01:07:01.060
I don't know anymore.

01:07:01.060 --> 01:07:02.960
I'm a comic book expert,
Patricia.

01:07:02.960 --> 01:07:05.790
I believe comic books are
a continuation of documentation

01:07:05.800 --> 01:07:09.900
that has gone on for centuries
of what humans are capable of.

01:07:09.900 --> 01:07:15.100
That they are what someone
somewhere saw or felt.

01:07:15.110 --> 01:07:17.770
Are you aware that spandex,
the underwear on the outside,

01:07:17.780 --> 01:07:22.380
and boots come from strongmen
in the circus in the 1930s?

01:07:22.380 --> 01:07:23.980
- No.
- The freak show men

01:07:23.980 --> 01:07:26.250
who could do
incredible feats of strength.

01:07:26.250 --> 01:07:30.520
I urge you to look past the
capes and monologuing villains.

01:07:30.520 --> 01:07:32.250
Are you with me?

01:07:32.260 --> 01:07:34.460
Yes.

01:07:34.460 --> 01:07:36.230
I only have a minute left.

01:07:36.230 --> 01:07:38.860
I believe The Beast
may be part of this.

01:07:38.860 --> 01:07:41.360
There are references
to man/animal characters.

01:07:41.370 --> 01:07:45.130
The dual character, the man
who has abilities like animals.

01:07:45.140 --> 01:07:48.140
I'd like to meet The Beast,
see if he's real.

01:07:48.140 --> 01:07:50.410
- <font color="#ff00ff">(PATRICIA GASPS SOFTLY)</font>
- If he is,

01:07:50.410 --> 01:07:54.280
then I'll get us all
out of here tomorrow night.

01:07:54.280 --> 01:07:56.250
<font color="#ff00ff">(SNIFFLES)</font>

01:07:58.450 --> 01:08:01.080
What's upsetting you, Patricia?

01:08:01.090 --> 01:08:03.890
<font color="#138ce9">PATRICIA:</font> What if he can't do
these extraordinary things?

01:08:06.590 --> 01:08:10.290
What if he is just unwell?

01:08:10.290 --> 01:08:12.000
Like you.

01:08:13.900 --> 01:08:18.600
Everything extraordinary
can be explained away,

01:08:18.600 --> 01:08:22.300
and yet it is true.

01:08:22.310 --> 01:08:24.439
I think deep down
you know this.

01:08:24.439 --> 01:08:28.979
Everything we will see and do
will have a basis in science.

01:08:28.979 --> 01:08:30.979
But it will have limits.

01:08:30.979 --> 01:08:33.920
This is the real world,
not a cartoon.

01:08:33.920 --> 01:08:38.920
And yet some of us
don't die from bullets.

01:08:38.920 --> 01:08:43.330
Some of us
can still bend steel.

01:08:43.330 --> 01:08:47.260
That is not a fantasy.

01:08:47.260 --> 01:08:50.100
Hmm.

01:08:50.100 --> 01:08:53.540
If you really think
you can get us all out,

01:08:53.540 --> 01:08:56.609
then you may meet The Beast.

01:08:56.609 --> 01:09:00.310
But for your sake,
I hope he likes you.

01:09:02.250 --> 01:09:04.950
Tomorrow night.

01:09:04.950 --> 01:09:07.850
Call a board meeting
or whatever.

01:09:10.090 --> 01:09:13.060
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHEELS SQUEAKING SOFTLY)</font>

01:09:13.060 --> 01:09:15.930
What do we call you, sir?

01:09:18.630 --> 01:09:23.830
First name, "Mr."
Last name, "Glass."

01:09:29.240 --> 01:09:31.470
<font color="#ff00ff">(SCANNER BEEPS, ALARM BUZZES)</font>

01:09:31.479 --> 01:09:33.109
<font color="#ff00ff">(DOOR OPENS, LIGHTS THUMP)</font>

01:09:33.109 --> 01:09:35.109
- <font color="#ff00ff">(GRUNTS)</font> What's going on?
- <font color="#138ce9">DR. STAPLE:</font> Be careful.

01:09:35.109 --> 01:09:36.979
- What... Oh.
- Not too much pressure when restraining him.

01:09:36.979 --> 01:09:38.109
Dr. Staple, what are you doing?

01:09:38.120 --> 01:09:39.250
- It's a sedative.
- What?

01:09:39.250 --> 01:09:40.649
- I'm sorry to do this, Elijah.
- Ow!

01:09:40.649 --> 01:09:42.979
We saw footage of you
leaving your room last night.

01:09:42.990 --> 01:09:44.390
- No. No.
- It seems you have been duping us.

01:09:44.390 --> 01:09:46.390
I've moved up the procedure
to this morning.

01:09:46.390 --> 01:09:47.490
Wait, I...

01:09:47.490 --> 01:09:49.490
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHEELS SQUEAKING)</font>

01:09:49.490 --> 01:09:51.430
<font color="#ffff00">♪</font>

01:10:04.680 --> 01:10:07.410
<font color="#138ce9">DR. STAPLE:</font> Thank you
for being careful, everyone.

01:10:07.410 --> 01:10:09.150
Good luck, Elijah.

01:10:10.480 --> 01:10:12.680
<font color="#138ce9">DR. STAPLE:</font> Nothing essential
is going to change

01:10:12.680 --> 01:10:14.650
about who you are.

01:10:14.650 --> 01:10:16.950
I promise, my friend.

01:10:24.160 --> 01:10:27.030
<font color="#ff00ff">(SWITCHES CLICKING)</font>

01:10:27.030 --> 01:10:28.460
<font color="#ff00ff">(HIGH-PITCHED WHIRRING)</font>

01:10:28.470 --> 01:10:30.440
<font color="#ff00ff">(WHIRRING GROWS LOUDER)</font>

01:10:32.140 --> 01:10:34.140
<font color="#138ce9">MRS. PRICE:</font> <font color="#ff00ff">(DISTORTED)</font> Elijah!

